70
00:07:07,009 --> 00:07:09,009
- Oh. Excuse me.
- That's all right.

71
00:07:11,555 --> 00:07:13,555
Hey, that's not a bad view, huh?

72
00:07:16,937 --> 00:07:19,480
What did you think of the case?

73
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:21,480
I mean, it had a lot of interest for me.

74
00:07:21,608 --> 00:07:24,608
No real... dead spots.
You know what I mean?

75
00:07:25,612 --> 00:07:28,156
I tell you, we were lucky
to get a murder case.

76
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:30,156
I figured us for an assault or burglary.

77
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:32,036
Boy, they can be the dullest.

78
00:07:34,036 --> 00:07:35,036
Hey.

79
00:07:35,413 --> 00:07:36,081
That the Woolworth Building?

80
00:07:37,081 --> 00:07:38,081
That's right.

81
00:07:39,084 --> 00:07:40,084
Isn't that funny?

82
00:07:40,752 --> 00:07:43,213
You know, I've lived here all my life.
I've never been inside that.

83
00:07:43,213 --> 00:07:45,213
If you had to sort out all that junk...

84
00:07:45,382 --> 00:07:47,382
Like that thing with the movies.

85
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:50,550
- Yeah. You can say that again.
- And what about that business with the knife?

86
00:07:50,637 --> 00:07:53,598
I mean, asking grown-up people
to believe that kind of jazz, huh?

87
00:07:53,598 --> 00:07:56,142
Well, I expected that.
You know what we're dealing with.

88
00:07:56,142 --> 00:07:58,142
Yeah, I guess so.

89
00:07:58,687 --> 00:08:00,064
Well, your horn works.
Now try your lights.

90
00:08:02,064 --> 00:08:03,064
- What do you got, a cold?
- And how.

91
00:08:03,608 --> 00:08:05,608
These hot-weather colds can kill you.

92
00:08:05,901 --> 00:08:08,404
I can hardly touch my nose.
You know what I mean?

93
00:08:08,404 --> 00:08:11,033
I sure do. I just got over one.

94
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:14,033
Aw, come on. Mr.
Foreman, let's go here, huh?

95
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:16,579
Well, that guy's still in the bathroom.

96
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:19,499
Hey, what's new? I didn't get a chance
to see a paper this morning.

97
00:08:19,499 --> 00:08:20,499
Hmm?

98
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:23,170
I was only wondering
how the market closed.

99
00:08:23,170 --> 00:08:25,170
You got a seat on the Exchange?

100
00:08:25,964 --> 00:08:27,798
I'm a broker.

101
00:08:27,798 --> 00:08:32,261
I run a messenger service -
the Beck and Call Company.

102
00:08:32,261 --> 00:08:34,261
The name is my wife's idea.

103
00:08:34,471 --> 00:08:38,184
Got 37 men working.
Started with nothing.

104
00:08:38,184 --> 00:08:41,184
Okay, men, let's take our seats, huh?

105
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:46,442
Yeah, we can all get outta here
pretty quick, huh?

106
00:08:46,442 --> 00:08:49,442
I don't know about the rest of you, but I happen
to have tickets to that ball game tonight.

107
00:08:49,738 --> 00:08:51,655
Yanks and Cleveland.

108
00:08:51,655 --> 00:08:53,533
Yeah, we got this kid,
Modjelewski, in there.

109
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:55,284
Ooh, he's a real bull, this kid.

110
00:08:55,284 --> 00:08:57,284
You know - Phoom!

111
00:08:57,495 --> 00:08:59,495
A real jug handle. You know?

112
00:08:59,831 --> 00:09:02,167
Phoom!

113
00:09:02,167 --> 00:09:04,167
You're a real baseball fan, aren't you?
Huh? Yeah.

114
00:09:04,586 --> 00:09:06,129
Where do we sit here?

