00:09:06,129 --> 00:09:09,129
Well, I thought we'd sit in order,
you know, by jury numbers.

116
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:11,298
One, two, three, four, five -
so on, around the table.

117
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:13,135
If that's okay with you gentlemen.

118
00:09:13,135 --> 00:09:14,135
- Sure.
- What's the difference?

119
00:09:14,303 --> 00:09:17,303
- I think it's reasonable to sit in order.
- Let it be.

120
00:09:17,432 --> 00:09:19,432
- Number 12. Do I sit down here?
- Yeah. That's 12. We go around...

121
00:09:19,768 --> 00:09:23,104
- We start with you. One, right?
- One, yeah. Two, three, four, five, six.

122
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:25,104
What was your impression
of the prosecuting attorney?

123
00:09:25,523 --> 00:09:27,317
Okay. Two. You're two.

124
00:09:27,317 --> 00:09:28,317
I beg pardon?

125
00:09:28,567 --> 00:09:32,567
I thought he was really sharp, the way
he handled all those points one by one.

126
00:09:32,822 --> 00:09:35,033
Logical sequence.
I was very impressed.

127
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:39,033
I think he - he did an expert job.

128
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:42,120
A lot of drive too, you know?
Real drive.

129
00:09:42,206 --> 00:09:44,206
- Okay, fellas, can we hold it down a minute?
- Sure.

130
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:45,043
Uh, fellas.

131
00:09:46,043 --> 00:09:49,043
Say, we'd like to get started.
Gentleman at the window.

132
00:09:51,173 --> 00:09:53,173
- We'd like to get started.
- Oh, I'm sorry.

133
00:09:53,426 --> 00:09:57,179
Pretty tough to figure, isn't it?
Kid kills his father - bing, just like that.

134
00:09:57,179 --> 00:09:59,179
Aw, listen, you analyze the figures,
you'll see it happens all the time.

135
00:09:59,849 --> 00:10:01,849
They let those kids
run wild up there.

136
00:10:01,851 --> 00:10:04,645
Well, maybe it serves 'em right.
