137
00:10:04,645 --> 00:10:06,313
Is - Is everyone here?

138
00:10:06,313 --> 00:10:08,232
The old man is inside.

139
00:10:08,232 --> 00:10:10,232
Oh. Would you, uh,
knock on the door for him?

140
00:10:10,943 --> 00:10:12,943
You a Yankee fan?

141
00:10:12,988 --> 00:10:14,447
No. Baltimore.

142
00:10:15,447 --> 00:10:16,243
- Baltimore?
- Yeah.

143
00:10:18,243 --> 00:10:20,243
That's like being hit in the head
with a crowbar once a day.

144
00:10:22,538 --> 00:10:23,538
Who have they got?

145
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:26,375
No, I mean, who have they got
besides good groundskeepers?

146
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:27,003
Say, uh, we'd like to get started.

147
00:10:28,003 --> 00:10:31,003
Oh, forgive me, gentlemen.
I - I didn't mean to keep you waiting.

148
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,716
Baltimore?

149
00:10:33,716 --> 00:10:36,594
Okay, gentlemen,
if I can have your attention.

150
00:10:36,594 --> 00:10:39,594
You fellas can handle this thing
any way that you want to.

151
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:42,225
I'm, um - You know,
I'm not gonna make any rules.

152
00:10:42,225 --> 00:10:45,225
Uh, we can, well, discuss it first
and, uh, then vote on it.

153
00:10:45,602 --> 00:10:48,355
That's, of course, uh -
That's, uh, one way.

154
00:10:48,355 --> 00:10:51,355
And, uh, well, we can
vote on it right now, and...

155
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:53,400
I think it's customary
to take a preliminary vote.

156
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:57,657
Yeah, let's - Let's vote. Who knows?
Maybe we all can get outta here, huh?

157
00:10:57,657 --> 00:10:59,451
Uh-huh.

158
00:10:59,451 --> 00:11:02,451
Okay, then I think that, uh...

159
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:05,581
Of course you know that we have
a first-degree murder charge here...

160
00:11:05,581 --> 00:11:07,581
and if we vote the accused guilty...

161
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:11,086
uh, we've got to send him
to the chair.

162
00:11:11,086 --> 00:11:14,086
- Um, that's mandatory.
- I think we know that.

163
00:11:14,923 --> 00:11:16,759
- Let's see who's where.
- We might as well.

164
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:20,759
- Okay. Uh, anyone doesn't want to vote?
- All right with me.

165
00:11:21,764 --> 00:11:26,436
Okay. Then, uh, just remember that this
has to be 12 to nothing either way.

166
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:27,436
Um, that's the law.

167
00:11:27,979 --> 00:11:30,105
Okay, are we ready?

168
00:11:30,105 --> 00:11:33,105
Now, all those voting guilty,
please raise your hands.

169
00:11:37,113 --> 00:11:40,113
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven...

170
00:11:41,951 --> 00:11:44,620
eight, nine, 10, 11.

171
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:47,620
Okay. That's 11 guilty.

172
00:11:47,624 --> 00:11:49,293
Those voting not guilty.

173
00:11:50,293 --> 00:11:52,293
One. Right.

174
00:11:52,461 --> 00:11:54,461
That's 11 guilty. One not guilty.

175
00:11:55,673 --> 00:11:57,341
Well, now we know where we are.

176
00:11:57,341 --> 00:12:01,054
Boy, oh, boy. There's always one.

177
00:12:02,054 --> 00:12:04,054
So, what do we do now?

178
00:12:04,432 --> 00:12:06,351
Well, I guess we talk.

179
00:12:06,351 --> 00:12:07,351
Boy, oh, boy.

180
00:12:07,769 --> 00:12:09,066
You really think he's innocent?

181
00:12:13,066 --> 00:12:14,066
I don't know.

182
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:17,654
I mean, you sat in court with the rest of us.
You heard what we did.

183
00:12:17,654 --> 00:12:19,654
The kid's a dangerous killer.
You could see it.

184
00:12:19,864 --> 00:12:21,573
He's 18 years old.

185
00:12:21,573 --> 00:12:23,573
Well, that's old enough. Î—e...

186
00:12:23,743 --> 00:12:26,495
He stabbed his own father
four inches into the chest.

187
00:12:26,495 --> 00:12:28,495
They proved it
a dozen different ways in court.

188
00:12:28,831 --> 00:12:31,458
Would you like me to list them for you?

189
00:12:31,458 --> 00:12:32,458
No.

190
00:12:32,836 --> 00:12:34,004
Then what do you want?

191
00:12:35,004 --> 00:12:37,004
- I just want to talk.
- What's there to talk about?

192
00:12:38,006 --> 00:12:39,006
Eleven men in here think he's guilty.

193
00:12:39,426 --> 00:12:41,426
No one had to think about it twice
except you.

194
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:44,056
I want to ask you something.
Do you believe his story?

195
00:12:45,056 --> 00:12:47,056
I don't know whether I believe it or not.
Maybe I don't.

196
00:12:47,851 --> 00:12:49,519
So how come you vote not guilty?

197
00:12:49,519 --> 00:12:51,519
Well, there were 11 votes for guilty.

198
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:54,356
It's not easy to raise my hand
and send a boy off to die...

199
00:12:54,356 --> 00:12:56,356
without talking about it first.

200
00:12:56,525 --> 00:12:58,238
- Well, now, who says it's easy?
- No one.

201
00:13:00,238 --> 00:13:02,238
What, just because I voted fast?

202
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:04,490
I honestly think the guy's guilty.

203
00:13:04,993 --> 00:13:07,870
You couldn't change my mind
if you talked for a hundred years.

204
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:09,456
I'm not trying to change your mind.
It's just that...

205
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:12,456
We're talking about somebody's life here.

206
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:14,792
We can't decide it in five minutes.
Supposing we're wrong.

207
00:13:14,961 --> 00:13:16,462
"Supposing we're wrong."

208
00:13:16,462 --> 00:13:18,462
Supposing this whole building
should fall down on my head.

209
00:13:18,548 --> 00:13:20,384
- You can suppose anything.
- That's right.

210
00:13:21,384 --> 00:13:23,219
Look, what's the difference
how long it takes?

211
00:13:23,219 --> 00:13:25,219
Suppose we do it in five minutes.
So what?

212
00:13:25,889 --> 00:13:28,099
Let's take an hour.

213
00:13:28,099 --> 00:13:30,099
The ball game doesn't start till 8:00.

214
00:13:32,729 --> 00:13:33,065
Hmm?

215
00:13:36,065 --> 00:13:37,065
Who's got something to say?

216
00:13:37,984 --> 00:13:39,485
I'm willing to sit for an hour.

217
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:42,279
Great. I heard
a pretty good story last night.

218
00:13:42,279 --> 00:13:44,073
That's not why we're sitting here.

219
00:13:45,073 --> 00:13:48,073
All right, then you tell me.
What are we sitting here for?

220
00:13:49,870 --> 00:13:51,706
I don't know. Maybe no reason.

221
00:13:52,706 --> 00:13:56,251
Look, this kid's been kicked around
all of his life...

222
00:13:56,251 --> 00:14:00,251
you know, born in a slum,
mother dead since he was nine.

223
00:14:00,255 --> 00:14:02,255
He lived for a year and a half
in an orphanage when his...

224
00:14:02,549 --> 00:14:05,549
his father was serving a jail term
for forgery.

225
00:14:05,553 --> 00:14:07,553
It's not a very happy beginning.

226
00:14:07,971 --> 00:14:10,182
He's a - a wild, angry kid.

227
00:14:10,182 --> 00:14:11,182
That's all he's ever been.
And you know why?

228
00:14:11,976 --> 00:14:15,772
'Cause he's been hit on the head
by somebody once a day every day.

229
00:14:15,772 --> 00:14:17,066
He's had a -
He's had a pretty miserable 18 years.

230
00:14:18,066 --> 00:14:21,066
I - I just think we owe him a few words.
That's all.

231
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:24,110
I don't mind telling you this, mister.
We don't owe him a thing.

232
00:14:24,739 --> 00:14:27,739
He got a fair trial, didn't he?
What do you think that trial cost?

233
00:14:27,908 --> 00:14:30,078
- He's lucky he got it. You know what I mean?
- You know it.

234
00:14:31,078 --> 00:14:33,078
Now, look, we're all grown-ups in here.

235
00:14:33,498 --> 00:14:35,457
We heard the facts, didn't we?

236
00:14:35,457 --> 00:14:39,336
You're not gonna tell me that we're supposed
to believe this kid, knowing what he is.

237
00:14:39,336 --> 00:14:41,336
Listen, I've lived among them
all my life.

